<h1>Off The Plan</h1>
</sub_heading>
</div>
<div class="text parbase">
<p style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><a href="/Net/Documentum/products/home-loan-products/default.aspx">Back to Home Loan Products</a></span></p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> </span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>Description<br/> </b><br/> Off the plan purchases are best described as a 'buy now and pay later' method of acquiring a residential property. A potential home buyer can purchase a property that has not yet been built.<br/> <br/> These customers exchange contracts for a property from the description in the developer's plan. Generally, buyers are required to pay a 10% deposit upon exchange of contracts with the balance to be paid upon completion of the property which can take up to 18 months.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> </span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>Features</b></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The application should be treated as a home seeker until a satisfactory on completion valuation has been received and the customers financial details have been re-verified within 90 days prior to settlement.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> </span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>Loan options</b><br/> <br/> </span></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Standard Variable Rate</span></li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Extra Variable Rate </span></li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>Note:</b> Off the plan purchase is not available for guarantor's support. This restriction does not apply in the case of marital / de facto relationships<br/> </span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> </span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>Conditions</b><br/>  </span></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Loan approval is conditional based on the following being obtained, as a minimum:</span>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">A satisfactory 'on completion' valuation is conducted 90 days prior to settlement. Note: A 'final inspection' is not required prior to settlement.</span></li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Re-verification of the customer's financial details.</span></li>
</ul> </li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">If there are any changes to the security position and/or the repayment capacity, the approval may be withdrawn.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">When valuing 'off the plan' a valuer must:</span>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">note the off the plan purchase price and sale date.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">indicate whether they have sighted the contract of sale and special conditions.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">indicate the anticipated completion date of the development.</span></li>
</ul> </li>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">If not complete at the time of inspection the valuer must:</span>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">value the property 'as if complete' and ensure the report clearly indicates this detail.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">provide a detailed description of outstanding works</span></li>
</ul> </li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">For applications involving LMI, approval is extended to 6 months only. LMI approval lapses after the 6 months. After this time a new application must be completed.</span></li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The loan cannot be switched to another loan type until it has been funded.</span></li>
</ul>
